# WHY: drift-check vs Gemini. Gemini: 'the dot product IS a Hamming distance.' FALSE as built —
#   the signatures are real-valued projection centroids (R@K, K float), not sign-bits.
#   dot = r - 2*Hamming holds ONLY for +/-1 vectors. So we MEASURED the binarized form.

